currentDoc: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

currentSuggestions.original: JFK was one of the few presidents he admired and respected, so it would be an honor to meet him.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: JFK was one of the few presidents he admired and respected, so it would be an honor to meet him.

currentSuggestions.original: After all, this was the 21st century, and ghosts were only a thing of the past right?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: After all, this was the 21st century, and ghosts were only a thing of the past right?

currentSuggestions.original: Seeing one was a bit of a shock.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Seeing one was a bit of a shock.

currentSuggestions.original: He called the number and spoke with a man who identified himself as John F. Kennedy.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: He called the number and spoke with a man who identified himself as John F. Kennedy.

currentSuggestions.original: JFK in particular was known for supposedly returning to the White House from time to time but with such reports being dismissed as fiction or fearmongering.
